    "bio1": "Jonathan Sunde is Vice President of Operations and Engineering at Strato, Inc. His 14-year rail industry career started at Ellcon-National in Greenville, SC, working on brake systems and other freight car components. His recent work has been in support of Strato's existing product lines in brake systems and hoses, with a large focus on draft systems and lading protection. He has been involved with AAR committees to improve industry standards and practices to allow longer, heavier trains to carry sensitive cargo safely.",
    "bio2": "Jonathan holds a BSME from Clemson University.",
    "abstract1": "Railcar speed is controlled by tractive effort at each locomotive wheel, dynamic and air brakes at each locomotive wheel, and air brakes applied to every wheel of the consist. The combination of these mechanisms produces a varied response at every wheel-rail interface. We will discuss how these different braking systems function with regard to brake signal propagation, equalization time and pressure, braking ratios, and empty-load devices. Each of these functional areas have potential failure modes, each with unique 'tells' that carry over into standard railcar inspection criteria.",
